&gt;     //Value is coming as 2019-10-10T18:30:00.000Z 
    //which is a day behind the selected value      




The AngularJS date picker uses the local timezone when parsing the date.

To set the date to UTC, use the `ng-model-options` directive:

    &lt;input type=&quot;date&quot; ng-model=&quot;date1&quot;
           ng-model-options=&quot;{timezone: &#39;UTC&#39;}&quot;
    /&gt;

Then the AngularJS will encode the date as 00:00 hours Zulu instead of 00:00 hours India (which is 18:30 Zulu of the previous day).

For more information, see

- [AngularJS `ng-model-options` Directive API Reference](https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/directive/ngModelOptions#specifying-timezones)

